title: Problem multi animal training in DLC 2.2b5 and above
body:
OS: Windows 10, NVIDIA-SMI 452.06 Driver Version: 452.06 CUDA Version: 11.0 DeepLabCut Version: 2.2b5-8 Anaconda env used: python 3.6 'jess-multi-dlc I'm trying to train an existing dataset in deeplabcut using multianimal tracking, and its giving me the weirdest output I'm ever seen. I'm used to DLC at this point and never ran into an issue like this. It seems like theres a compatibility issue with TF and this new version of dlc. I've gone through the motions of normally labeling frames and checking them, building the skeleton, etc. The labor was done on a CPU and now I'm trying to train on my GPU (again, changed file names and everything, all that checks out). Can someone help? I really don't want to relabel a new dataset, as I've labeled a copious amount of frames
